Thus the Origin of the Gymnaſtic Arts is clearly unfolded, as being no more than a Part of the ſavage Song-Feaſt;
Feaſt; but ſeparated from thence for the Ends of warlike Service. For Want of this Information, the learned VOSSIUS, among other Authors, ſtiles the Dance a Branch of the Gymnaſtic, inſtead of regarding the Gymnaſtic as the Offspring of the Dance
De Nat. Art. l. i. c. 3. .
